Since the original Pull Request was opened as a fork in a contributor's repository, we are unable to create a Pull Request branching from it with only the style fixes. The following Restylers [made fixes](https://restyled.io/gh/TokTok/repos/toxic/jobs/434056): - astyle To incorporate these changes, you can either: 1. Merge this Pull Request *instead of* the original, or 1. Ask your contributor to locally incorporate these commits and push them to the original Pull Request
Expand for example instructions ```console git remote add upstream https://github.com/TokTok/toxic.git git fetch upstream pull//head git merge --ff-only FETCH_HEAD git push ```
**NOTE**: As work continues on the original Pull Request, this process will re-run and update (force-push) this Pull Request with updated style fixes as necessary. If the style is fixed manually at any point (i.e. this process finds no fixes to make), this Pull Request will be closed automatically. Sorry if this was unexpected. To disable it, see our [documentation][]. commit.message: Implement new groupchats (again) alongside old ones
Fix memory leak caused by improperly closing groups on exit and fix a private message display bug
Update peer_exit callback
Handle self-initiated moderation events client-side since callbacks are no longer triggered
Improve error handling for invalid moderator actions
Disable DHT node list updates temporarily
Remove groupchat ban commands
use test network bootstrap nodes list
Fix bug causing peer list not to be cleared on rejoin
Update for TCP-DHT groupchats
Fix bug causing topic change spam when there are sync issues
Fix bug causing kicked peer's name to show up as unknown to the kicker
Fix and improve group name fetching
Initialize peer_id
Fix bug causing incorrect name to be displayed on self group nick change
Rename all instances of groupnum -> groupnumber
Format fixes and variable name changes
No longer use API supplied groupnumbers to index groups
Update self role on group join and remove some unnecessary code
Group peer exit refactor
Add sync error group exit type
Add self_disconnected group exit type
Add group disconnect command
Add config setting for custom group part messages

rename groupchat.* groupchats.*

This is just to make merging with the master branch easier

modularize string arrays for line completion

Instead of using various different forms of string arrays and having to handle them
differently for string completion, we now always use char pointer arrays. This allows
us to remove some large stack allocations, remove a bunch of confusing defines that
keep track of global array sizes, and generally unclutters the code so it's easier
to read.

Fix a few issues

- realloc needs to be error checked
- use correct format specifiers
- make sure optarg and DATA_FILE aren't null before using them
Merge with master branch
